{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutexref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexRef"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":" can be statically allocated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is a version of our ","type":"text"},{"code":"give_me_next_number()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"],"syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"want to require prior calling to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", because your code","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", as that requires a prior call to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". In these cases you can also use a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It must be initialized with "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and freed with with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_free()"},{"type":"text","text":" when not needed anymore to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"platforms.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used even if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-1udyo","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-2xtcf","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-7fh5d","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-8whsh","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(_:)-98jdd","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/ptr"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef\/StaticMutexProtocol-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"metadata":{"title":"StaticMutexRef","symbolKind":"struct","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","externalID":"s:4GLib14StaticMutexRefV","fragments":[{"kin